name: Create detailed specifications before major development
scope: markdown
language: markdown
severity: error
if: Starting major feature development without detailed specification
then: Create comprehensive specification with phases, tasks, design principles, and success metrics
why: Detailed specifications prevent scope creep, ensure clear goals, and improve development efficiency.
globs: ["docs/**/*.md"]

---
name: Keep specifications code-free
scope: markdown
language: markdown
severity: warning
if: Specification contains implementation code
then: Remove code and focus on goals, tasks, and design principles
why: Specifications should focus on what to build, not how to build it.
globs: ["docs/**/*.md"]

---
name: Include success metrics in specifications
scope: markdown
language: markdown
severity: warning
if: Specification without measurable success criteria
then: Add specific, measurable success metrics
why: Success metrics ensure clear completion criteria and enable validation.
globs: ["docs/**/*.md"]

---
name: Use phase-based development structure
scope: markdown
language: markdown
severity: warning
if: Specification without clear phases
then: Structure specification with logical phases (Foundation, Feature, Polish, Integration, Optimization)
why: Phase-based development ensures logical progression and clear milestones.
globs: ["docs/**/*.md"]

---
name: Include design principles in specifications
scope: markdown
language: markdown
severity: warning
if: Specification without design principles section
then: Add design principles that guide implementation decisions
why: Design principles ensure consistent decision-making during implementation.
globs: ["docs/**/*.md"]

---
name: Reference existing patterns in specifications
scope: markdown
language: markdown
severity: info
if: Specification doesn't reference existing patterns
then: Reference existing patterns from Design Guidelines where appropriate
why: Leveraging existing patterns improves consistency and reduces reinvention.
globs: ["docs/**/*.md"]
description:
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---
